# Cloudflare Pages redirects/rewrites — clean URL support
#
# Cloudflare Pages serves .html files at their extensionless path
# automatically in most cases, but this file makes the behavior
# explicit and guarantees it works even if that default ever changes,
# if the project is later moved behind a Worker/Function, or if
# another static host (Netlify also reads this same _redirects
# format) is used instead.
#
# Format: source  destination  status-code
# A 200 status means "rewrite" (serve this file, keep the URL the
# user sees as-is) rather than "redirect" (which would change the
# URL in the address bar back to .html — the opposite of what we want).

/about      /about.html      200
/shop       /shop.html        200
/leather    /leather.html     200
/contact    /contact.html     200
/product    /product.html     200
/terms      /terms.html       200

# Catch-all: if nothing above or no static file matches, fall back to
# the custom 404 page (Cloudflare Pages already does this by default,
# but it's made explicit here too).
/*    /404.html   404
